snippet.textDisplay: Ayeee I have a similar “hair piercing skin” story. I was sitting on my bed and my dog was on the floor next to me. I was wearing socks and I felt some uncomfortableness in my left foot, so I tried moving the sock around to get rid of it. It didn’t go away and so I pulled off my sock to see what was causing the problem. Well, somehow my dog’s hair got stuck in my foot and I had to pull it out. It even caused a small welt. I told my mom about it and she kept insisting it was a weird mutation with me but I knew it was my dog’s hair because it faded from a deep blonde to a white. I’m all good now, lol.

snippet.textDisplay: What. Yes, I've been pierced by a hair before. It went all the way into my pinky toe, and I noticed pain in it during the first day. I looked at it the first day, and noticed nothing, no swelling, nada. I thought I had stepped on a piece of glass or something, but couldn't find anything. After a week of dealing with the constant pain, I checked my toe again, and lo and behold, a single thin hair was poking out of the pad of my toe. I grabbed it, gave it the gentlest of tugs, and it came through. No follicle, no gross pus, nothing. Somehow a hair got in my pinky toe. I'm still mystified on how it happened.

snippet.textDisplay: I have also have thick hair, and I also was (unfortunately) born with natural blonde streaks in my hair. It is SO ANNOYING having to wash it. It weighs my head down, and before it can do that it has to be under water for around 10 minutes before it is actually wet. The only real perk was the fact you could style it in a lot of ways, but BEFORE you could style it you had to brush it. Lemme tell you something real quick folks. DO. NOT. BRUSH. THICK. HAIR. WITH. A. COMB. It is a nightmare waiting to happen. You touch a single hair on your head with one of those flimsy things, and you hair devours the comb. I eventually got sick of it all and cut it to just above my shoulders. Mind you, this whole hair cut took about an hour, and by the end of it all I had enough hair to make a wig with. So yeah. Thick hair is great.
